  "prompt": "What is the oldest book ever written?",
  "response": "The oldest known written book is generally considered to be \"The Epic of Gilgamesh.\" This ancient Mesopotamian epic poem dates back to around 2100 BCE and was written on clay tablets in cuneiform script. It is a compilation of stories that were passed down through oral tradition before being transcribed. The work originates from the Sumerian civilization in the region that is now modern-day Iraq. While there might have been older texts in different forms, \"The Epic of Gilgamesh\" is one of the earliest known literary works that has survived in a form recognizable as a \"book.\"",
